isEmpty

public static boolean isEmpty(Object $obj)
Checks whether a value is empty

If you pass a Number (that is, a primitive type or something that implements Number), this method will check whether it is equal to zero or not.

If you pass a String, this method will check whether it is the empty string (and return true) or not (and return false).

If you pass null if will return true.

isNull

public static boolean isNull(Object $obj)
Checks whether the given value is null or not.

Thanks to autoboxing you can do so with primitive data-types, too. This function is needed in automatically generated code, where it may be unknown whether the type is a primitive one or not (primitive types can not be compared to null using ==).
